ETC / "Edit To Configure" / "Editable Text Configuration":
/etc/mailcap - default programi za extensne
$HOME/.bashrc - mesto za bash aliase in funkcije
/var/log/auth.log - logini
/etc/passwd - userji
/etc/groups - grupe

SERVICES:
/etc/init/, $HOME/.init/ - init - Upstart init daemon job configuration
/etc/init.d/ - direktorij z service skriptami ki se zazenejo ob zacetku in koncu
/etc/init.d/halt - se zazene ob koncu
/etc/rc<NUM>.d - Startup scripts for different runlevels - links to scripts in /etc/init.d - S85httpd -> S means startup, K is for stop. (To disable service just change S for K)
/etc/rc.local - last initialization file executed - put your commands here

/etc/init/ssh.conf - sshd config
/etc/ssh/sshd_config - sshd config
~/.bash_profile  - for PATH, JAVA_HOME (ali .bashrc) for one user
	/etc/profile OR /etc/bash.bashrc - for all users 
/etc/fstab - Automatic mounts are handled by configuring the file
/etc/sudoers - lists of users and the commands they can run with sudo
/etc/crontab - system-wide crontab
/etc/cron.hourly|daily|weekly|monthly/ - links to scripts that will execute periodicaly. Scripts within a cron directory are run alphabetically.
/etc/rsyslog.conf|rsyslog.d/50-default.conf - log conf (need to restart rsyslogd after edit)
/etc/services - list of services with their port numbers
/etc/resolv.conf - dns information

PROC / The files under the /proc show various information
about the system:
/proc/cpuinfo - information about the CPU
/proc/modules -  information about what kernel-modules are loaded on your system
/proc/net/ - network related
	/proc/net/route - routing table
	netstat - Displays contents of /proc/net files
/etc/syslog.conf - Configuration information for syslogd 

USR - "Unix System Resources":
/usr/lib/jvm - java jres and jdks
/usr/share/man - man pages

SBIN - the "system-administrator's bin file", which hosts programs that would be in /bin if they didn't have "root-only"
access permissions.

VAR - "variable":
/var/log/ - System logs in here
/var/log/auth.log - log loginov
/var/log/syslog - večina ostalih logov
/var/spool - contains data which is awaiting some kind of later processing

BOOT (kernels):
/boot/grub/menu.lst - Grub configuration file


